2019 was an exciting year in the South Africa IT and telecommunications market with many exciting developments and big changes. This year saw Rain launching the country’s first commercial 5G products and Telkom starting to roam on Vodacom’s network. Cell C, which continues to struggle financially, concluded a new agreement with MTN which gives it nationwide roaming. Another big development was MultiChoice’s listing on the Johannesburg Stock Exchange (JSE) – the first new listing in 2019. 2019 was also a year where many South African companies and government institutions were targeted by cyber-criminals. A group which called itself “Shadow Kill Hackers” compromised the City of Johannesburg’s IT systems and demanded a ransom to not leak data which they said they stole. Local Internet service providers (ISPs) were also targeted by cybercriminals through DDoS attacks that saw many broadband users left without connectivity. To give an overview of these events and others which shaped the South African IT and telecoms market, here are the biggest stories of the year. Rain launched its new 5G service in September, offering “unlimited ultra-fast Internet” with speeds of up to 700Mbps. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-325773" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Rain-5G-unbox-header.jpg" alt="Rain 5G unbox header" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Rain-5G-unbox-header.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Rain-5G-unbox-header-300x202.jpg 300w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Rain-5G-unbox-header-595x400.jpg 595w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> In November, Telkom confirmed that it was in discussions with Cell C to acquire the embattled mobile network. Shortly afterwards Cell C rejected Telkom’s offer, but some Cell C shareholders still want the deal to go through. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-307598" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Telkom-logo-presentation.jpg" alt="Telkom logo presentation" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Telkom-logo-presentation.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Telkom-logo-presentation-300x202.jpg 300w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Telkom-logo-presentation-595x400.jpg 595w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> MultiChoice Group listed on the JSE on 27 February 2019. MultiChoice Group CEO Calvo Mawela blew the market’s “kudu horn” to mark the occasion, following JSE representatives stating there was phenomenal interest in the listing. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-297636" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Calvo-MultiChoice.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Calvo-MultiChoice.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Calvo-MultiChoice-300x202.jpg 300w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Calvo-MultiChoice-595x400.jpg 595w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> Internet service providers in South Africa fell prey to massive distributed denial of service (DDoS) attacks in 2019. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-189026" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/DDoS-text-hack.jpg" alt="ddos-text-hack" width="640" height="430" /> Large chunks of South African Internet Protocol address space, worth millions of dollars on the open reseller market, has been stolen or is being squatted on by unscrupulous overseas network operators. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-241014" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Mimecast-Cybercriminal.jpg" alt="Mimecast Cybercriminal" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Mimecast-Cybercriminal.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Mimecast-Cybercriminal-300x202.jpg 300w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Mimecast-Cybercriminal-595x400.jpg 595w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> The Competition Commission published a final report on its Data Service Market Inquiry in December. The  Commission stated that the biggest mobile operators in the country – Vodacom and MTN – must drop their prices. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-200194" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Vodacom-MTN-smartphones.jpg" alt="Vodacom MTN smartphones" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Vodacom-MTN-smartphones.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Vodacom-MTN-smartphones-300x202.jpg 300w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Vodacom-MTN-smartphones-595x400.jpg 595w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> Community Investment Ventures Holdings (CIVH), which is 54% owned by Remgro and 35% by NewGX, is growing into a South African telecommunications powerhouse with very valuable assets. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-263807" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Pieter-Uys.jpg" alt="Pieter Uys" width="640" height="427" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Pieter-Uys.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Pieter-Uys-600x400.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> Discovery Bank unveiled its three banking accounts in July – Discovery Gold Card, Discovery Platinum Card, and Discovery Black Card  – with prices ranging between R90 and R325 per month. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-300396" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Discovery-Bank.jpg" alt="Discovery Bank" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Discovery-Bank.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Discovery-Bank-300x202.jpg 300w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Discovery-Bank-595x400.jpg 595w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> In October, Mara Phones officially opened the first smartphone manufacturing facility in South Africa, located in Durban, KwaZulu-Natal. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-324126" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Mara-Phone-gold-header.jpg" alt="Mara Phone gold header" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Mara-Phone-gold-header.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Mara-Phone-gold-header-300x202.jpg 300w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Mara-Phone-gold-header-595x400.jpg 595w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> Wi-Fi network provider VAST Networks shut down in late 2019. After years of seeking a buyer for the floundering company, Dimension Data and Naspers decided to pull the plug. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-282615" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/VAST-Networks_MyBroadband_.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/VAST-Networks_MyBroadband_.jpg 640w, https:/